  <prompt>
    Wave 11 starts here. Before any code edits, audit how PlaybookOrchestrationService resolves
    template expressions today and design the RunContext.NodeOutputs surface that Wave 11 will
    introduce. The audit must answer: what does ApplyConfigJsonTemplates do today? What context
    is available at each ExecuteNodeAsync call? Where would node outputs need to be collected
    and re-exposed for downstream nodes? Output is a design doc the next tasks (111, 112, 113,
    114) execute against — they should not need to re-read source to start.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET backend developer familiar with the Spaarke BFF playbook orchestration model
    and Handlebars.NET. Goal: extract the exact wiring decisions, not re-implement.
  </role>

  <goal>
    A design document at `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/spikes/wave11-orchestrator-resolution-design.md`
    that answers:
    1. What does `PlaybookOrchestrationService.ApplyConfigJsonTemplates` (line ~1921) do today, and what does it NOT do?
    2. What does `ITemplateEngine.Render(template, context)` accept as context, and what helpers does the existing `TemplateEngine.cs` already register?
    3. What is the proposed `RunContext.NodeOutputs` shape? (`IDictionary<string, object?>` keyed by `OutputVariable` name → JsonElement-converted output value via `TemplateEngine.ConvertJsonElement`)
    4. At which point in the orchestrator loop do node outputs get registered, and what type does the orchestrator pass to subsequent template-engine renders?
    5. Which Handlebars helpers must be added (per deployed DAILY-BRIEFING-NARRATE playbook configJson scan)? List concretely.
    6. Does the fan-out iteration semantic (`iteration.iterateOver` + `iteration.itemAlias`) live in the orchestrator or in the template engine? (Per Wave 11 plan: orchestrator.) Justify briefly.
    7. What's the minimum-viable test plan for each subsequent task (111 / 112 / 113 / 114)?
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="orchestrator">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PlaybookOrchestrationService.cs</file>
    <file purpose="template-engine-impl">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/TemplateEngine.cs</file>
    <file purpose="template-engine-iface">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/ITemplateEngine.cs</file>
    <file purpose="run-context">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PlaybookRunContext.cs</file>
    <file purpose="executor-iface">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Nodes/INodeExecutor.cs</file>
    <file purpose="node-output">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Nodes/NodeOutput.cs</file>
    <file purpose="deployed-playbook-source">projects/spaarke-daily-update-service/notes/playbooks/daily-briefing-narrate.json</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/plan.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI Minimalism — `ITemplateEngine` is already registered in DI. No new abstraction layers. Wave 11 uses it; does not wrap it.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">BFF AI Architecture — orchestrator stays in BFF; no new service surface introduced.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-037">Multinode Output Composition — fan-out iteration semantic must align with composeStrategy as documented in the playbook source JSON `composeStrategy.fanOut` block.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §11">Audit only — do NOT introduce new components in this task. Component justification triple applies to subsequent tasks where applicable.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §10">Audit task does not modify BFF; no publish-size check needed for this task.</constraint>
  </constraints>

