    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Existing Handlebars.NET helpers" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/TemplateEngine.cs">
        Engine already exists. Registers `default`, `safe`, `joinIds`. Supports `{{X.Y.Z}}` nested access natively. Has `ConvertJsonElement` for JsonElement → Dictionary/List conversion.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Current orchestrator template resolution" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PlaybookOrchestrationService.cs">
        `ApplyConfigJsonTemplates` at line ~1921 only does literal `{{paramName}}` string replacement against `runContext.Parameters` (IReadOnlyDictionary&lt;string,string&gt;). Does NOT use `ITemplateEngine`. Does NOT carry node outputs.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Wave 10 task 100 marked 15 success criteria GREEN at the verification report level, but Wave 10 task 101 (UAT) hit empty `/narrate` responses end-to-end. Investigation 2026-06-29 traced root cause to the orchestrator: `ApplyConfigJsonTemplates` only handles literal `{{paramName}}` substitution. The deployed `DAILY-BRIEFING-NARRATE` playbook uses richer expressions (`{{json start}}`, `{{tldrResult.summary}}`, `{{map …}}`, fan-out iteration) that go unresolved. LLM nodes see literal template strings as their payload and return empty content.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="Wave 5" status="complete">94 nodes backfilled with sprk_executortype (executor dispatch ready).</dependency>
      <dependency task="Wave 8" status="complete">PlaybookBuilder UI deployable (Power Apps form changes for executorType).</dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>R4 worktree `spaarke-daily-update-service-r4` HOLDS open until Wave 11 + Wave 10 task 101 close R4 graduation gate (FR-15).</item>
      <item>Existing TemplateEngine.cs (Handlebars.NET-based) was built for delivery nodes (email/Word templates). Wave 11 extends its usage into the orchestrator without forking.</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Rigor Declaration">
      Output: 🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: STANDARD · 📋 REASON: audit + planning, no source mod, design doc only · Proceeding with Step 0...
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Load context">
      Read project CLAUDE.md + plan.md (Wave 11 section) + bff-extensions.md.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Read orchestrator template-resolution today">
      Read `PlaybookOrchestrationService.cs` focusing on: `ExecuteAsync`/`ExecuteNodeAsync` loop, `ApplyConfigJsonTemplates` (line ~1921), `RunContext` field references. Document what `runContext.Parameters` carries and what's missing.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Read existing TemplateEngine.cs + ITemplateEngine.cs">
      Document the existing helpers (`default`, `safe`, `joinIds`), the `Render` API, and the `ConvertJsonElement` JsonElement-to-Dictionary helper. Note: Handlebars.NET supports `{{X.Y.Z}}` natively + subexpressions `{{helperA (helperB arg) arg}}`.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Read PlaybookRunContext.cs + NodeOutput.cs + INodeExecutor.cs">
      Identify where to add `NodeOutputs` collection. Confirm NodeOutput shape (StructuredData? TextContent?). Confirm executor return contract.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Scan deployed DAILY-BRIEFING-NARRATE source JSON for required helpers">
      Read `projects/spaarke-daily-update-service/notes/playbooks/daily-briefing-narrate.json`. Enumerate every distinct `{{helperName …}}` shape. Confirm: `json`, `map`, `flatten`, `distinct`, `concat`, `join`, fan-out (`iteration.iterateOver`/`itemAlias`), `lambda` (T113 eliminates via `flatMap` rewrite).
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Write design doc">
      Create `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/spikes/wave11-orchestrator-resolution-design.md` answering all 7 goal questions. Include code snippets for: proposed `RunContext.NodeOutputs` shape, proposed `ApplyConfigJsonTemplates` rewrite signature using `ITemplateEngine`, proposed helper registrations, iteration semantic placement. Target: 150-200 lines.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Update current-task.md + TASK-INDEX">
      Mark task 110 ✅; advance current-task.md to task 111.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Commit">
      Commit notes/spikes/wave11-orchestrator-resolution-design.md with conventional message. No PR yet (Wave 11 commits incrementally per task).
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
